## Running Backend Tests

### Prerequisites
Make sure you are in the root directory:
```
'cd ..' all the way back to the root directory.
```

Install all dependencies:
```
pip3 install -r backend/requirements.txt
```

> Note: This should install everything required to run the backend, including unit tests

### Environment Setup
Set up the '.env', there is an .env example that can be used as a template.
```


### Running Tests
```bash
PYTHONPATH=. python3 -m pytest backend/backUnitTest/ -v
```